To solve the Knight's Tour problem efficiently for an $m \times n$ board (defaulting to $8 \times 8$), we can use a backtracking algorithm enhanced with **Warnsdorff's Rule**. This heuristic suggests that the knight should always move to the square from which it will have the fewest onward moves. This significantly reduces the search space and finds a solution almost linearly.

